            <scopecontent>
                <p>Many of the poems in this album are written by friends of Mary Swords and are
                    often dedicated to her and in praise of her friendship. Other topics of poetry
                    include love, death and love lost. A few of the poems note New York in the
                    signature line. The volume is also extra-illustrated with a few engravings with
                    romantic subjects, such as an Arabian knight on horseback.</p>
            </scopecontent>


